txt.en:
'Been waitin' for a shipment of healing supplies, but I haven't seen nor heard any sign of it. Scouts reported Orcs carrying the crates off to their camp, Hanksar-mokh, to the west. And now I have more injured dwarves than supplies to spare.

'I'm thinkin' you can get the supplies back, though. Whatever is left in those crates should be easy enough to carry on your own.

'I'd wager the Orcs keep the supplies close at hand while resting at their camp-fires.'
The healer Thrúthug is running out of supplies to ease the pain of injured scouts.
You have retrieved the remaining healing supplies.\n\nYou should bring them to Thrúthug at Drenghól.
'Nicely done. I'll put these to good use.'

Hanksar-mokh is located to the west of Drenghól.\n\nYou should retrieve the healing supplies from stolen crates across their encampment. Thrúthug believes you'll find the crates near their camp-fires.
